	<h2>Spacing</h2>
	<p>
		Astro UXDS spacing tokens use increments of four to define all dimensions,
		padding, and margins for components, containers, grids, and other UI
		elements. The design tokens are based on a 4 px system where 1 token step
		equals .25 rem, which equals 4 px by default. For example, the <code
			>spacing-4</code
		> token equals 1 rem (16 px by default).
	</p>

	<p class="note">
		When building components, Astro UXDS uses the border-collapse method for
		sizing. In this method the borders overlap the padding within a component,
		as opposed to the box model method where the borders are added in addition
		to the padding. So in Astro UXDS, a component with 8 px padding and 2 px
		border would only have 8 px of spacing.
	</p>

